LEX Escrow.

"Buyer" is	 a person.
"Seller" is A person.
"Agent" is  a person.
"Service Fee" is	aN  amount.

The Buyer pays an amount into escrow, appoints the Seller, appoints the Agent, and fixes the Service Fee.

CLAUSE: Pay Out.
The Agent may pay from escrow the Service Fee to themselves, and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the Seller.

CLAUSE: Pay Back.
The Agent may pay from escrow the Service Fee to themselves, and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the Buyer.

